   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SF-MAYOR (San Francisco) _ San Francisco Mayor Willie Brown,
viewed as a competent leader who can keep the economy humming,
leads challenger Tom Ammiano, seen as a champion of the little guy
who understands voters' everyday concerns, a San Francisco
Examiner/KTVU poll shows. By The San Francisco Examiner.
</P>
<P>
   HOLOCAUST-INSURERS (San Francisco) _ Insurance Commissioner
Chuck Quackenbush on Tuesday is expected to subpoena as many as 15
large European-based insurance companies concerning policies
written for the victims of the Holocaust and their survivors. By
The San Francisco Examiner.
</P>
<P>
   FEATURES/LIFESTYLE (``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CHICKEN-RANCHES (Petaluma, Calif.) _ In decades past, when
Petaluma's chicken ranches gave it the nickname ``Egg Basket of the
World,'' millions of chickens sprang from its acres of cavernous
coops. The poultry industry has long since flown those coops. Now,
artists, artisans and fledgling entrepreneurs are renting them,
scraping off layers of chicken poop and using them as prized studio
space. By VICKI HADDOCK.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SHAQ (San Francisco) _ In a season when so many teams and
players are paying homage to the late Wilt Chamberlain _ with
shoulder patches, headbands, retired numbers _ Shaquille O'Neal
should follow suit with his own unique tribute. He should try
shooting free throws underhand. Either that, or stop whining about
getting mauled under the basket. By JORGE L. ORTIZ.
</P>
<P>
   OUTDOORS-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ After being rebuffed in calls
to four county sheriff offices for a clarification of road law,
here is a challenge not only to sheriffs, but to the highway patrol
and police departments: Provide a simple, black-and-white
explanation of right-of-way when cars meet bikes on country roads
in the foothills _ and I will print it. By TOM STIENSTRA.
</P>
