<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`MUSSOLINI' LACKS DRAMA; `AUSTIN POWERS' STILL FUN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Tea With Mussolini'' (DVD) _ Despite a fine
cast, headed by Maggie Smith, Judi Dench, and Joan Plowright (who
pitch a shutout against the two Americans, Cher and Lily Tomlin),
Franco Zeffirelli's pre-World War II recollections all seem
unconnected and, frankly, undramatic.
</P>
<P>
   ``Austin Powers: The Spy Who Shagged Me'' _ Not quite as groovy
as the original, but Mike Myers is a very funny, courageous star.
Who else would have the nerve to look so dorky? Those teeth! That
hair!
</P>
<P>
   ``The Barry Levinson Collection'' _ This set, priced at under
$45, includes ``Avalon,'' ``Diner,'' and ``Tin Men.'' The
Baltimore-based director made these three autobiographical movies
in his hometown. The fourth, ``Liberty Heights,'' opens in theaters
on Friday. While ``Avalon'' doesn't quite make it, ``Diner'' and
``Tin Men'' are two of the best working-class comedies around.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Last Picture Show'' (DVD) _ Peter Bogdanovich took
Hollywood by storm with this provocative adaptation of the Larry
McMurty novel that captured the stark beauty and deep-seated drama
of growing up in a small town in Texas. Cybil Shepherd, Jeff and
Beau Bridges, Cloris Leachman, and Ben Johnson head up a terrific
ensemble cast, and Bogdanovich offers illuminating commentary.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NEW ON DVD: ``The Crossing Guard,'' ``Five Easy Pieces,''
``Grand Illusion,'' ``The Loss of Sexual Innocence,'' ``Monty
Python's Flying Circus'' (sets 3 and 4), ``Peeping Tom,'' ``The
Third Man.'' Out on Nov. 23 _ ``Apocalypse Now,'' ``Beavis &AMP;
Butt-head Do America,'' ``Caligula'' (unrated and R-rated
editions), ``Chinatown,'' ``Entrapment,'' ``Heavy Metal,'' ``Lady
and the Tramp,'' ``The Last of the Mohicans,'' ``Limbo,'' ``The
Love Letter,'' ``A River Runs Through It,'' ``South Park: Bigger,
Longer &AMP; Uncut.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Nov. 23: ``The Haunting,'' ``The Iron
Giant,'' ``The Autumn Tale,'' ``The Draughtsman's Contract'' (DVD),
``A Zed and Two Noughts'' (DVD), ``Entrapment,'' ``South Park:
Bigger, Longer and Uncut.'' Nov. 30: ``The Wild Wild West,'' ``Deep
Blue Sea.'' Dec. 7: ``Hoods,'' ``Inspector Gadget.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-11-15-99 1407EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
