<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Eds.: To bolster your coverage of the war in Chechnya, The New
York Times Syndicate recommends the following op-eds: by Russian
Prime Minister Vladimir Putin, who sets forth a moving defense of
the war, and by Pavel Palazchenko, a noted commentator, who writes
that the most disturbing aspect of the war is that the top military
commanders seem to be out of control. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   -- Both articles have moved on the wire in the ``k'' commentary
and ``a'' general news categories. --
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHY RUSSIA MUST ACT IN CHECHNYA &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; By VLADIMIR PUTIN &LR;  &QC;   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Terrorism today knows no boundaries. Its purveyors collaborate
with each other over vast distances. ... We know that Shamil
Basayev, the so-called Chechen warlord, gets assistance on the
ground from an itinerant guerrilla leader with a dossier similar to
that of Osama bin Laden. ...
</P>
<P>
   ``No government can stand idly by when terrorism strikes. It is
the solemn duty of all governments to protect their citizens from
danger. Americans obviously understand this concept.'' (slugged:
BC-OP-ED-CHECHNYA-PUTIN-NYTSF)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; IS THE MILITARY OUT OF CONTROL IN CHECHNYA? &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; By PAVEL PALAZCHENKO &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   ``Continuing public support for this war, which has resulted in
a sharp rise in the popularity of Prime Minister Vladimir Putin, is
disturbing. It is of course natural for any nation to rally in
support of its soldiers. But people seem to be too eager to swallow
the crude official propaganda, and the media too willing to play
along.
</P>
<P>
   ``What's more, top officers ... have publicly and not too subtly
warned of possible mutiny and even civil war should their hard-line
campaign be thwarted by the political leadership in Moscow. This,
for the Russian military, which typically steers clear of politics,
is extremely unusual behavior, and it is the most disturbing aspect
of the war.'' (slugged: BC-CHECHNYA-REFUGEES-ARMY-NYTSF &LR; )
</P>
<P>
   ...............................
</P>
