<P>
   &UR; Eds.: To bolster your coverage of the war in Chechnya, The New
York Times Syndicate recommends the following op-eds: by Russian
Prime Minister Vladimir Putin, who sets forth a moving defense of
the war, and by Pavel Palazchenko, a noted commentator, who writes
that the most disturbing aspect of the war is that the top military
commanders seem to be out of control. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   -- Both articles have moved on the wire in the ``k'' commentary
and ``a'' general news categories. --
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHY RUSSIA MUST ACT IN CHECHNYA &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; By VLADIMIR PUTIN &LR;  &QC;   &QL;
