   SCOTUS-PRAYER (Washington) _ The decades-old debate over school
prayer finally cycled back to the Supreme Court on Monday in the
form of a singularly American question, one that has as much to do
with culture as with either religion or law: does it violate the
Constitution for one student to lead others in prayer before a
public high school football game? The court announced today that it
would hear a small Texas school district's appeal from a federal
appeals court's ruling that barred the highly popular and deeply
entrenched practice of pre-game invocations. By Linda Greenhouse.
