<P>
   ATM-FEES (Santa Monica, Calif.) _ This oceanside suburb of Los
Angeles last month passed the nation's first local ordinance
banning banks from charging non-customers for using their ATMs. San
Francisco voters approved a similar measure earlier this month, and
now, politicians in many other cities are said to be looking at
proposing similar bans. In New York, City Council speaker Peter
Vallone said on Monday that he plans to propose an ordinance
similar to the ones in California. The Department of Defense has
also proposed a ban on such surcharges on all military bases. But
the banking industry is fighting to squelch the uprising before it
gathers more steam. By Andrew Pollack.
</P>
