<HEADER>
A0522 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s BC-FBC-BCS16-COX     11-15 0392
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-BCS16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Hokies gain ground after Tennessee loss; FSU on topBy Tony
Barnhart
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Tennessee's 28-24 loss to Arkansas on Saturday was the opening
Virginia Tech needed. The Hokies moved into the No. 2 spot behind
Florida State in the Bowl Championship Series rankings released
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Tennessee (7-2), No. 2 last week, dropped to fifth. That loss,
plus Virginia Tech's 43-10 beating of Miami, moved the Hokies to a
solid No. 2. Virginia Tech is expected to finish no worse that
second if it wins its final two games, against Temple (2-7) and
Boston College (7-2).
</P>
<P>
   The rankings are determined by totaling four components: a
team's average position in the two major opinion polls, media and
coaches; its average position in eight computer polls; a point
total derived from a formula to determine strength of schedule; and
its won-loss record.
</P>
<P>
   The lower the total score, the better the ranking. The top two
teams in the final rankings, released Dec. 5, will play for the
national championship Jan. 4 in the Sugar Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Florida State (10-0), ranked No. 1 in all but one of the polls
used in the formula, can lock up one of those spots by beating No.
4 Florida on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Nebraska (9-1) is ranked fourth in both major polls but moved
past Florida (9-1) into the No. 3 spot from No. 6, on the strength
of its 41-15 win over previously unbeaten Kansas State. The
Cornhuskers have one game left, against Colorado on Nov. 26. A win
would put them in the Big 12 championship game against Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Florida is .59 points behind Nebraska but should make a big jump
if it knocks off Florida State. If it beats Florida State and then
wins the SEC championship game _ the opponent probably will be No.
6 Alabama _ Florida might have to hold its breath to see if it has
done enough to hold off Nebraska for the other Sugar Bowl slot.
</P>
<P>
   Georgia Tech (7-2) is No. 13 but has a good chance to jump into
the top 12 with Penn State and Michigan State, No. 11 and No. 12,
respectively, playing each other on Saturday. To qualify for an
at-large BCS bid, a team must have at least nine wins and be in the
top 12 of the BCS rankings.
</P>
<P>
   Tony Barnhart writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
