   DAM-FISH (Undated) _ A panel of scientists assembled by the
federal government says punching holes in four Snake River dams in
southeastern Washington is the best way to help endangered salmon
there. But that conclusion drew unmerciful fire in the region and
in the halls of Congress. So this week federal fisheries managers
will tell Pacific Northwesterners, in effect: ``OK, you figure out
what to do.'' They will offer a menu of other, equally unpleasant
