<P>
   OVERTIME-POLICE (Los Angeles) -- After six years fighting its
biggest lawsuit ever, Los Angeles city officials are nearing an
agreement to pay police officers a record $40 million to settle an
overtime dispute stemming from the riots. Facing prospects of Y2K
trouble and the Democractic Convention next August, city officials
are preparing to settle the federal lawsuit that claims the city
paid officers months late for overtime earned during the 1992
riots. It also claims officers often are given compensatory time
off instead of overtime pay, but are not allowed to use it in a
timely manner. By Dominic Berbeo. (Will move on the ``n''
California news wire.) (TENTATIVE)
