   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Tuesday, Nov. 16. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
AIMS (Phoenix) - Only 11 percent of Arizona students who took the
state's AIMS educational proficiency test as sophomores last spring
met the the test's math academic standards. In reading, 61 percent
hit or exceeded the necessary bar, while in writing, 30 percent
did.
</P>
<P>
   In a Monday press conference, the state's education chief called
the results ``unsettling'' but not surprising. By KELLY PEARCE.
Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
