recently completed twin in Hanford, Wash., are called LIGO
(pronounced LIE-go), for Laser Interferometer Gravitational-wave
Observatory. At $296 million so far, it is the largest enterprise
ever financed by the National Science Foundation. (California
Institute of Technology/New York Times Photo)
