   (NYT3) NEW YORK -- Nov. 15, 1999 -- SCI-HEART-MONITORS-2, 11-15
-- A wrist watch heart-rate monitor can help determine exercise
efficiency. No exerciser should be without one, says Gregory Florez
of the American Council on Exercise, a nonprofit group that reports
on fitness and certifies personal trainers and aerobic instructors.
``After clothing to cover your body, a heart-rate monitor is the
single most essential piece of fitness equipment,'' Florez says.
(Don Hogan Charles/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- Nov. 15, 1999 -- SCI-HEART-MONITORS-1, 11-15
-- Robert St. Thomas, an exercise specialist at Plus One Fitness at
