help determine exercise efficiency. To help exercisers avoid either
overdoing or underdoing it, experts advise establishing a target
training zone: 50 to 90 percent of maximum heart rate, the fastest
your heart is capable of beating. (Don Hogan Charles/New York Times
Photo)
