<SLUG> BC-HOME-IMPROVEMENT-BUDGET-ADV05-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BUDGET: HOME IMPROVEMENT QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS
</HEADLINE>
  By BERNARD GLADSTONE 
 Copyright 1999 Bernard Gladstone 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
 (PLEASE NOTE: To publish Bernard Gladstone's ``Home Improvement
Questions and Answers'' it must be purchased _ the rate is not
prohibitive _ from New York Times Syndication Sales. For purchase
information call toll-free 1-888-269-8796.) 
 (The NYTSS sales representative also has information on how to
subscribe to Gladstone's ``Home Improvement Questions and Answers''
weekly column which moves on Wednesdays.) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   This column moved today:
</P>
<P>
   BERNARD GLADSTONE'S ``HOME IMPROVEMENT QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS''
for Sun., Dec. 5, 1999, which included:
</P>
<P>
   _How a plumb bob on a chalked cord will tell you if those book
shelves you're building are level (comes with illustration).
</P>
<P>
   _How to fix that maddening rattle in the bathroom exhaust fan.
</P>
<P>
   _Using oil to restore the original dark finish on aluminum
siding? Not a good idea.
</P>
<P>
   _Installing windows that will keep out daytime heat _ and
curious stares.
</P>
<P>
   NOTE: Art work accompanies all Gladstone ``Home Improvement''
columns.
</P>
<P>
   Questions about home-repair problems should be addressed to
Bernard Gladstone, care of The New York Times Syndication Sales
Corp., 122 E. 42nd St., New York, N.Y. 10168. Questions of general
interest will be answered in this column; Mr. Gladstone regrets
that unpublished letters cannot be answered individually.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (PLEASE NOTE: To publish Bernard Gladstone's ``Home Improvement
Questions and Answers'' it must be purchased _ the rate is not
prohibitive _ from New York Times Syndication Sales. For purchase
information call toll-free 1-888-269-8796.) &QL; 
 &UR; (The NYTSS sales representative also has information on how to
