<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EARLY SELECTIONS INSPIRATIONAL?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ In an effort to focus on UCLA as quickly as
possible, USC coach Paul Hackett named juniors Brent McCaffrey and
Markus Steele captains for the game just moments after the Trojans
defeated Washington State.
</P>
<P>
   The move might be viewed as inspirational, but it also could be
interpreted as a possible slight at the seniors, who were
criticized earlier this season by Hackett.
</P>
<P>
   Player reaction was mixed.
</P>
<P>
   ``Coach Hackett's making the decisions and Brent's playing well,
so I guess he deserves it. I was just happy I got to be a captain
twice,'' senior offensive lineman Travis Claridge said. ``I think
it would be cool for all the seniors to go out there, but we can't
do that. In Coach Hackett's defense, guys that are playing well
deserve to represent us.''
</P>
<P>
   Said senior wide receiver Windrell Hayes: ``I wasn't really
surprised. I don't think he goes by seniority. I don't really think
about it like that.''
</P>
<P>
   Added another player, who asked not to be identified: ``I think
a senior deserves to be captain. Of course, we've talked about
it.''
</P>
<P>
   Two seniors _ tailback Chad Morton and free safety David Gibson
_ will also represent USC along with junior strong safety Ife
Ohalete, because they are permanent captains.
</P>
<P>
   __ Collarbone comparison: Hackett said USC and UCLA faced
similar situations by losing their starting quarterbacks with
broken collarbones, although USC lost to Oregon and UCLA defeated
Washington.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is exactly what happened to us in Oregon. But we were on
the road and they were at home. Washington was nice enough to turn
the ball over four times,'' Hackett said. ``I would say they have a
lot of momentum with (Ryan McCann). They did a good job of
coaching.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it's shaping up as an exciting game. There's so many
similarities.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Bring on Wolverines? Hackett said he had no objections to
USC's attempts to gain a spot in the Kickoff Classic against
Michigan to open next season.
</P>
<P>
   ``I couldn't be happier if it happens,'' Hackett said. ``We
would start practicing earlier and Carson (Palmer) would get to
practice sooner.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Nearing 1,000: Tailback Chad Morton needs 86 yards in USC's
final two games to gain 1,000 yards. He would be the Trojans' third
tailback of the 1990s to reach 1,000 yards, joining Mazio Royster
(1,168 yards in 1990) and Delon Washington (1,109 in '95).
</P>
<P>
   __ Dubious record: For only the fourth time in the USC-UCLA
rivalry, both teams are entering the game with losing records. The
last time it happened was in 1941.
</P>
<P>
   __ Singled out: Hackett was impressed with the efforts of
defensive back Antuan Simmons and converted tight end Matt Welch
against Washington State.
</P>
<P>
   Simmons went 72 plays despite having a sore back, and Welch
participated in 48 plays after Antoine Harris went out with a
strained hamstring.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
